 "default": false, "description": "Relevant to the compiler team, which will review and decide on the PR/issue."}, {"id": 650731663, "node_id": "MDU6TGFiZWw2NTA3MzE2NjM=", "url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rust-lang/rust/labels/C-bug", "name": "C-bug", "color": "f5f1fd", "default": false, "description": "Category: This is a bug."}], "state": "closed", "locked": false, "assignee": null, "assignees": [], "milestone": null, "comments": 1, "created_at": "2019-07-30T17:49:22Z", "updated_at": "2019-09-20T11:39:03Z", "closed_at": "2019-09-20T11:39:03Z", "author_association": "MEMBER", "active_lock_reason": null, "body": "If I do ...\r\n\r\n```rust\r\nfn main() {\r\n    let x = \"hello\";\r\n    let y = Box::new(*x);\r\n}\r\n```\r\nI get the following error ...\r\n\r\n```\r\n --> src/main.rs:3:13\r\n  |\r\n3 |     let y = Box::new(*x);\r\n  |             ^^^^^^^^ doesn't have a size known at compile-time\r\n  |\r\n  = help: the trait `std::marker::Sized` is not implemented for `str`\r\n  = note: to learn more, visit <https://doc.rust-lang.org/book/ch19-04-advanced-types.html#dynamically-sized-types-and-the-sized-trait>\r\n  = note: required by `std::boxed::Box::<T>::new`\r\n```\r\n\r\nI think the right error should be ...\r\n\r\n```\r\n --> src/main.rs:3:13\r\n  |\r\n3 |     let y = Box::new(*x);\r\n  |                      ^^ doesn't have a size known at compile-time\r\n  |\r\n  = help: the trait `std::marker::Sized` is not implemented for `str`\r\n  = note: to learn more, visit <https://doc.rust-lang.org/book/ch19-04-advanced-types.html#dynamically-sized-types-and-the-sized-trait>\r\n  = note: required by `std::boxed::Box::<T>::new`\r\n```\r\n\r\nIs not that `Box` is not `Sized`, the problem is that the parameter of the `Box`'s `new` function is not `Sized`. So the last note in the error is important and also kind of lost in a lot of noise.\r\n\r\nPossibly related to #61860.", "closed_by": {"login": "bors", "id": 3372342, "node_id": "MDQ6VXNlcjMzNzIzNDI=", "avatar_url"